The aspiring food truck entrepreneur is planning to serve two types of sandwiches - type A and type B in his food truck. He has noticed that the demand for type A sandwich is three times the demand for type B sandwich. He wants to ensure that he doesn't run out of sandwiches and decides to make sandwiches in batches each day. 

He is planning to make $a$ batches of type A sandwiches and $b$ batches of type B sandwiches each day, where $a$ and $b$ are positive integers. He has budget constraints and can afford to make at most $N$ batches of sandwiches each day ($N$ is a positive integer). The entrepreneur wants to maximize the number of type A sandwiches while ensuring that he doesn't exceed his budget. 

The entrepreneur's problem can be modeled as the following integer programming problem:

\begin{align*}
\text{maximize } & 3a + b \\
\text{subject to } & a + b \leq N \\
& a, b \geq 0 \\
& a, b \in \mathbb{Z}
\end{align*}

Determine the optimal solution for $a$ and $b$ that maximizes the total demand while ensuring that the constraints are satisfied.
